definition: to make (some time or space) available (for sb)
to soar/to gallop/to prance/to turn over/to vacate/to clear

to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc
to get one's hands free (to do sth else)

sentences.english: Yes, we have a two-room apartment free after the weekend.
sentences.chinese: 對，這個週末以後我們可以騰出一套兩居室的公寓。

sentences.english: We can free up $20,000 for new computer equipment.
sentences.chinese: 我們可以騰出2萬圓買新的電腦設備。

sentences.english: Vargas emptied his tool bag and left the bag with the Indian.
sentences.chinese: 瓦格斯騰出自己的工具袋，把它留給印第安人。

sentences.english: Now, Mother has to take off all her time and take care ofher.
sentences.chinese: 現在呢，媽媽得騰出大部分時間來照顧她。

sentences.english: To simplify the Chinese people, combined to free his left hand, cater to other things.
sentences.chinese: 中國人化繁爲簡，合二爲一，騰出左手，兼做別事。

sentences.english: They have razed those buildings to make way for the new highway.
sentences.chinese: 他們拆除了那些建築物以便騰出地方修建新的公路。

sentences.english: Whatever your dreams are – make time for them, and treat them seriously.
sentences.chinese: 不論你的夢想是什麼，都要爲它騰出時間，認真對待。

sentences.english: The children squeezed together to make room for me to sit down.
sentences.chinese: 孩子們擠在一起以便騰出空來讓我坐下。

sentences.english: Just eliminate the negative thoughts and you’ll make room for some more positive thoughts.
sentences.chinese: 排除消極思想，爲積極思想騰出空間。

sentences.english: Release the seat she is still a smile so bright with happiness.
sentences.chinese: 騰出座位的她依舊是笑得那麼的燦爛與幸福。

sentences.english: Set aside some time each week to talk about staying home alone.
sentences.chinese: 每個星期騰出一點時間和孩子聊聊一個人在家的情況。

sentences.english: I’ll keep Friday night free and we can go then.
sentences.chinese: 我將把週五晚上騰出來，到時候我們就能去了。

sentences.english: The chewing of the gum will keep your mouth busy and spare your fingers.
sentences.chinese: 嚼口香糖會讓你的口腔繁忙，也能騰出你的手指頭了。

sentences.english: The gray-beard swept out an arm to clap Shemsen on the shoulder.
sentences.chinese: 灰鬍子騰出一隻手，拍了拍舍姆森的肩。

sentences.english: Making time for reading religious and sacred texts is a challenge in our own time.
sentences.chinese: 而我們的時代，騰出時間閱讀宗教經書卻是件難事。

sentences.english: The singers bunched up to make room for one more.
sentences.chinese: 這些歌手擠在一起，騰出了一個人的空間。
